Pacquiao, meanwhile, made his latest appearance on Kimmel's talk show and delighted the audience with a rendition of his walk-in song.

Written by the boxer himself, the song is called 'I Fight for the Filipino People' and Kimmel even joined in with the 36-year-old.

Pacquiao and Mayweather have come face-to-face just once in the build-up, at the press conference to announce the fight.

Mayweather will make the short trip from his gym to the MGM Grand next week while Pacquiao will fly in from his Los Angeles base.

